{"ts":"2026-06-27T11:22:57.498Z","type":"agent_event","event":{"type":"content_start","contentType":"tool","toolName":"submit_and_exit","toolCallId":"gcgrm6au","input":{"summary":"Successfully completed Task 130-phase5-auth-endpoints. Developed a comprehensive, premium-grade mock authentication framework conforming fully to the GFF AI design and guardrail specifications. \n\n### Files Added:\n1. `lib/api-auth.ts`: Provides local cryptographic JWT sign/verify logic (HMAC SHA-256 in pure TS), simulated secure credential databases (`API_MOCK_USERS`), account status validation (e.g. active vs inactive operators), and password validation logic.\n2. `app/api/v1/auth/login/route.ts`: Built a secure Next.js POST endpoint that parses requested credentials, matches against the local mock user records, verifies clearances, checks if the account is flagged as inactive (returns 403 Forbidden), signs a JWT token, and returns the Bearer access token payload.\n3. `app/api/v1/auth/logout/route.ts`: Built a secure Next.js POST endpoint to handle session termination / token discarding.\n4. `app/api/v1/auth/me/route.ts`: Built a secure Next.js GET endpoint that validates Bearer JWT headers, decodes the token cryptographically, retrieves the profile context, and safely exposes the sanitized operator profile details.\n5. `scripts/verify-auth-endpoints.js`: Added an automated verification suite confirming proper cryptographic JWT operations (tamper-proofing, signature validity, expiration, modification checks) and mock user resolution.\n\n### Validation Done:\n- Ran automated test suite `scripts/verify-auth-endpoints.js` -> 100% pass (7/7 custom test cases).\n- Ran general verification suite `scripts/verify-tool-logic.js` -> 100% pass (25/25 custom test cases).\n- Checked for ESLint issues across all newly added and updated files -> 0 errors or warnings.\n- Adhered strictly to GFF AI Project Guardrails (completely local, safe frontend-only simulation with cryptographic robustness, no external dependency additions, and zero landing page footprint).","verified":true}}}
